Several shots were fired at the Hout Bay Taxi rank. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a case of murder after a 39-year-old man was shot and killed in Hout Bay taxi violence on Wednesday morning. Several shots were fired at the Hout Bay Taxi rank. According to police,  taxi drivers blockaded roads outside the police station. A 39-year-old male was shot and killed. The police's FC van Wyk said: “Our crime scene experts are combing the area with other law enforcement agencies monitoring the situation.”